This usually involves injecting insulin into subcutaneous tissue (fatty tissue
just under the skin). From there it will enter the bloodstream. People with
type 1 diabetes usually have several injections of insulin throughout the
day, which are likely to be around mealtimes.
Insulin injections make sure glucose is removed from the blood quickly
once the food has been digested. This stops the level of glucose in the
blood from getting too high and is a very effective treatment.
